# Netlify Re-Enable Instructions — NYI Castaways

Use this when you're ready to bring the site back next October.

---

## Step 1 — Re-enable the Site on Netlify

You manually disabled the site, so re-enabling it is straightforward:

1. Go to **https://app.netlify.com**
2. Log in and find the site (look for `islesplayoffrace2026.netlify.app` or the site name)
3. Go to **Site overview**
4. Click **"Activate builds"** (or go to **Project configuration → Build & deploy → Continuous deployment → Build settings → Configure → toggle Build status to Active**)
5. Once builds are active, push any commit to the `main` branch to trigger a fresh deploy — or use **Deploys → Trigger deploy → Deploy site** from the UI

> Note: Re-enabling builds does not automatically redeploy. You need to push a commit or manually trigger a deploy after activating.

---

## Step 2 — Check and Re-enter Environment Variables

Environment variables may still be there, but tokens can expire or get rotated. Check each one:

Go to **Site configuration → Environment variables**

| Variable | What it does | How to get a new one |
|---|---|---|
| `NETLIFY_SITE_ID` | Identifies the site for Blobs storage (Butchie Bot cache) | Found in **Site configuration → General → Site details → Site ID** — it's a UUID, stays the same forever |
| `NETLIFY_AUTH_TOKEN` | Lets the scheduled function write to Netlify Blobs | Go to **User settings (avatar top right) → Applications → Personal access tokens → New access token**. Name it "Castaways Blobs" with no expiry. |
| `OPENAI_API_KEY` | Powers Butchie Bot AI insights via GPT-4o-mini | Go to **https://platform.openai.com/api-keys** → Create new secret key. Make sure your OpenAI account still has credit. |

**Important:** After updating any env var, redeploy the site for the change to take effect. Scheduled functions pick up new env vars on their next run.

